{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775848162993,"sessionID":"ses_28733c4faffe3d66rps1PQCQ3M","part":{"id":"prt_d78cc86ae0012tYKgkscz5Z1hW","messageID":"msg_d78cc7ff2001e5zmoLtJmyEShx","sessionID":"ses_28733c4faffe3d66rps1PQCQ3M","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848178110,"sessionID":"ses_28733c4faffe3d66rps1PQCQ3M","part":{"id":"prt_d78cc89f9001LiO4FOX6qqIrhh","messageID":"msg_d78cc7ff2001e5zmoLtJmyEShx","sessionID":"ses_28733c4faffe3d66rps1PQCQ3M","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_d1e609b1d5a040ba8c68ab6a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Delta Spec: AR-010 — Router 会话管理\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session management in `pkg/router`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-010\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe router module requires session management to maintain stateful connections and track client sessions to backend services.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Session Storage\n\n### Scenario: Router creates session for new client\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with session management enabled\n**WHEN** a new client connects without a session ID\n**THEN** the router SHOULD generate a unique session ID\n**AND** store session state for the client\n\n### Scenario: Router retrieves existing session\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with active sessions\n**WHEN** a client reconnects with a valid session ID\n**THEN** the router SHOULD restore the session state\n**AND** route the request to the same backend\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Session IDs are generated uniquely\n- [ ] Sessions persist across requests\n- [ ] Sessions are cleaned up on expiration\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775848178096,"end":1775848178108}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848178114,"sessionID":"ses_28733c4faffe3d66rps1PQCQ3M","part":{"id":"prt_d78cca8af0019rOjWgMMoa3ooE","messageID":"msg_d78cc7ff2001e5zmoLtJmyEShx","sessionID":"ses_28733c4faffe3d66rps1PQCQ3M","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_7039e0ba3e924d7195f08657","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/router  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-1 (Planning)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Session Storage\n\n- [ ] **1.1** TBD — Define session data structure\n- [ ] **1.2** TBD — Implement session storage backend\n- [ ] **1.3** TBD — Add session creation/retrieval methods\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Session Lifecycle\n\n- [ ] **2.1** TBD — Implement session expiration\n- [ ] **2.2** TBD — Add session cleanup mechanism\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Session-Based Routing\n\n- [ ] **3.1** TBD — Route requests to consistent backend based on session\n- [ ] **3.2** TBD — Handle session affinity\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- TBD\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-010/delta-spec.md`","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775848178100,"end":1775848178111}}}}
